text: Interstate 695 (I-695) is a auxiliary Interstate Highway that has a beltway extending around Baltimore, Maryland, United States. It is called the Baltimore Beltway. The route is an auxiliary route of I-95, intersecting that route southwest of Baltimore near Arbutus and northeast of the city near White Marsh. The Francis Scott Key Bridge that crossed over the Patapsco River was included in this section of the route before the bridge collapse on March 26, 2024. ==References== Category:Interstate Highways
